<br>
@triangle123 - What's your read on Paschendale?

@Melmond, yes, I will post when I'm back.<br>
<br>
@Khan, He sounds like a VT until day 3, where he has something to do at night. I seriously can't think of any roles that it might be. I think it is town though, if mafia or cult leader than he would have stuff to do at night. <br>
<br>
Or maybe he is cult, not cult leader, but I don't know what he has to do on night 3.

@Khan, what if he roleclaims PR? <br>
<br>
@Melmond, look at my reasons.

@Cheery Dog: we aren't lynching pieceofpecanpiece today, so I dontknow why you're wasting valuable pre-deadline time talk to and about him.<br>
<br>
Tell (or link) me the reason that you're voting Hellhound1.

@pappums rat: Pieceofpecanpie's timing of his outrageous "confirmed town" statement means he's either a townie playing really badly or he's scum setting up a distraction.<br>
<br>
Either way, we get better informationas a town if the discussion is centered on potential lyncheesthan not.

@pappumsrat, The replacement does not have Hellhound's personality, does he? We cannot lynch him while a replacement is searching because:<br>
1. Hellhound has poor defenses, replacement might have strong ones. <br>
2. We cannot judge a replacement by the last user that had his/her role.

@CheeryDog, I said I would do that later. But I kind of gave up because you guys said my reads sucked <img class="smilies" src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" width="15" height="15" alt=":(" title="Sad"><br>
<br>
@triangle, sure. I voted him because mainly, because of his vote on me and his stupid post about giving me pressure. I also voted him because pecan told me to, though that wasn't as huge as that post.

Because he worked really really hard on it and no one's even said that they're going to put it up on the fridge door with magnets.<br>
<br>
@Idiotking I'll re-read and get on that soon

Oh while I think of it.<br>
<br>
